All Classes

Class Summary 
Class Description
Battleship
Creates the Battleship class which is an an extension form the Ship class
BattleshipGame
Main game class - Where all the game play happens.
Cruiser
Creates the Cruiser class which is an extenion of the Ship class
Destroyer
Creates the Cruiser class which is an extenion of the Ship class
EmptySea
Empty Sea is a class that is derived from Ship EmptySea serves a "catch-all" ship filling in the spaces in the game board array where there is no ship.
Ocean
The Ocean class represents the game board for Battleship Ocean holds the variables for the game including the ocean size, number of battleships, number of cruisers, number of destroyers, and number of submarines.
OceanTest
Java tests for the Javacript game.
Ship
The Ship class is comprised of objects generated for the player to interact with on the Gameboar All of the ships and the EmptySea are subclasses of Ship
ShipTest
Test of all ship-related classes
Submarine
Creates the Submarine class which is an an extension form the Ship class
